cs.AI, cs.PL, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.SY. 

The paper discusses techniques for planning in domains specified with PDDL2.1, which is a language commonly used in artificial intelligence for planning. Therefore, cs.AI is the most likely sub-category. The paper also focuses on temporal planning and introduces a graph-based representation called TA-graphs, which falls under the sub-category of cs.PL (programming languages). The use of stochastic local search and multi-criteria quality plans suggests that the paper may also fall under the sub-categories of cs.LG (machine learning) and cs.RO (robotics). Finally, the paper discusses the experimental results of the 3rd International Planning Competition, which suggests that it may also fall under the sub-category of cs.SY (systems and control).
